The paper deals with transfer learning and fine-tuning of deep neural networks for image classification tasks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The proposed approach involves using a recurrent gated network to selectively fine-tune convolutional filters, which is a technique that falls under the category of adaptive learning (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) experiments using pre-trained models, which could potentially place it in the sub-categories of neural networks (cs.NE) or computational linguistics (cs.CL).
